{{redirect|drum-song|the 1978 album|Drum Song|the 2009 song|Drumming Song|songs named "Drum"|Drum (disambiguation)}}
{{confused|Gucci (disambiguation){{!}}Gucci}}
In [[Chinese culture]], '''Guci''' ({{zh|s=鼓词|t=鼓詞|p=Gǔcí|l=drum lyrics}}) are the [[prose|prosimetric]] lyrics of ''[[dagu (music)|dagu]]'', one musical entertainment form in the ''[[shuochang]]'' or "speak and sing" genre. The performers narrate a story based on the lyrics, usually accompanied by singing, while beating a [[drum]]. Other accompanying musical instruments are [[sanxian]], [[sihu (instrument)|sihu]], [[pipa]] and [[yangqin]]. The art form was very popular during the [[Ming Dynasty]] and [[Qing Dynasty]],<ref>Hegel, Robert E. (1998). ''Reading Illustrated Fiction in Late Imperial China.'' [[Stanford University Press]]. pp.26, 371-372.</ref> and therefore extant ''guci'' are very important in studying Chinese fiction from those period.<ref>Hanan, Patrick. (2004). ''Chinese Fiction of the Nineteenth and Early Twentieth Centuries: Essays.'' [[Columbia University Press]]. p.134.</ref>

